{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Gal|5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","chapter":5,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":1,"text":"For freedom, Christ set us free. Stand firm, then, and don’t submit again to a yoke of slavery.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":2,"text":"Take note! I, Paul, am telling you that if you get yourselves circumcised, Christ will not benefit you at all.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":3,"text":"Again I testify to every man who gets himself circumcised that he is obligated to do the entire law.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":4,"text":"You who are trying to be justified by the law are alienated from Christ; you have fallen from grace.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":5,"text":"For we eagerly await through the Spirit, by faith, the hope of righteousness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":6,"text":"For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision accomplishes anything; what matters is faith working through love.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":7,"text":"You were running well. Who prevented you from obeying the truth?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":8,"text":"This persuasion does not come from the one who calls you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":9,"text":"A little leaven leavens the whole batch of dough.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":10,"text":"I myself am persuaded in the Lord you will not accept any other view. But whoever it is that is confusing you will pay the penalty.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":11,"text":"Now brothers and sisters, if I still preach circumcision, why am I still persecuted? In that case the offense of the cross has been abolished.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":12,"text":"I wish those who are disturbing you might also let themselves be mutilated!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":13,"text":"For you were called to be free, brothers and sisters; only don’t use this freedom as an opportunity for the flesh, but serve one another through love.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":14,"text":"For the whole law is fulfilled in one statement: Love your neighbor as yourself.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":15,"text":"But if you bite and devour one another, watch out, or you will be consumed by one another.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":16,"text":"I say, then, walk by the Spirit and you will certainly not carry out the desire of the flesh.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":17,"text":"For the flesh desires what is against the Spirit, and the Spirit desires what is against the flesh; these are opposed to each other, so that you don’t do what you want.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":18,"text":"But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":19,"text":"Now the works of the flesh are obvious: sexual immorality, moral impurity, promiscuity,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":20,"text":"idolatry, sorcery, hatreds, strife, jealousy, outbursts of anger, selfish ambitions, dissensions, factions,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":21,"text":"envy, drunkenness, carousing, and anything similar. I am warning you about these things —as I warned you before —that those who practice such things will not inherit the kingdom of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":22,"text":"But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":23,"text":"gentleness, and self-control. The law is not against such things.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":24,"text":"Now those who belong to Christ Jesus have crucified the flesh with its passions and desires.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":25,"text":"If we live by the Spirit, let us also keep in step with the Spirit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":5,"verse":26,"text":"Let us not become conceited, provoking one another, envying one another.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","chapter":5,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,13,16,19,22],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Freedom of the Christian"},{"beforeVerse":16,"text":"The Spirit versus the Flesh"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:5:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For freedom, Christ set us free. Stand firm, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 14:4","book":"Rom","chapter":14,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Php 1:27","book":"Php","chapter":1,"verse":27,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" then, and don’t submit again to a yoke of slavery. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 4:22","book":"Gal","chapter":4,"verse":22,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","tex